BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.levyparkhouston
 .org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Event-Lawn-with-Screen-scaled.png
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/wp-content/uploads
 /2026/05/Event-Lawn-with-Screen-scaled.png
UID:6U73ygc0AI8022IVw3rBv
SUMMARY:Summer Soccer Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260617T064055Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260620T080000
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the world’s greatest soccer tournament playin
	g out in Houston and cities across North America\, Levy Park is getting in
	to the festivities with free game watch parties. This series of 15 curated
	\, family-friendly watch parties offers a central gathering place for fùtb
	ol fans to catch some of the tournament’s most anticipated games\, includi
	ng key matchups featuring the United States and Mexico\, as well as pivota
	l knockout rounds. Each free viewing event will feature a large-scale outd
	oor LED screen with professional sound\, entertainment\, food and beverage
	 concessions\, and merchandise sales. \nCommunity Partners: Further enhanc
	ing programming\, Levy Park will partner with local organizations to broad
	en community engagement\, including collaborations with cultural groups an
	d soccer-focused nonprofits. Levy Park is seeking enthusiastic volunteers 
	and community partner organizations to help bring this festival to life. V
	olunteers will work directly alongside our event team\, supporting booth o
	perations and helping ensure every guest has an unforgettable experience. 
	Email us to learn more about volunteer opportunities. \nFood and Beverage 
	Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer and wine\, and n
	on-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. Visit Smalls Sliders for burgers\, 
	fries\, and shakes and cool down with Frios Gourmet Pops. Stop by Hearsay’
	s festival tent for a cold beer or beer bucket or grab a michelada\, wine\
	, or beer from Gaspacho’s festival tent. Non-alcoholic drinks from Coca-Co
	la as well as pre-packaged snacks can be purchased at the Community Partne
	r Concessions Booth\, proceeds benefiting Levy Park and the event’s commun
	ity partners. \nFace Painting & Henna Art: Get into the tournament spirit 
	with face and body art! \nMerchandise: Event merchandise celebrating Houst
	on\, Levy Park\, and the global soccer tournament will also be available f
	or purchase. \nArt Installations and Photo Opportunities: Commemorate the 
	experience with a photo tour of the park\, including life-sized soccer-the
	med photo backdrops and a tournament bracket. Visit our soccer ball music 
	box and turn the crank for festive sounds. \nFestival Guidelines: \nVISITO
	RS MUST COMPLY WITH DIRECTIONS FROM PARK PERSONNEL\, OR THEY WILL BE ASKED
	 TO LEAVE THE PARK. PARENTS ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THEIR CHILDREN’S SAFETY IN
	 THE PARK. \nCHAIRS AND SEATING: No outside furniture. Blankets may be bro
	ught into the Festival site for the designated blanket seating area. All o
	ther furniture is available on a first-come\, first-served basis. \nSTROLL
	ERS & WAGONS: Oversized strollers and wagons may need to be parked in a de
	signated area during the festival. All visitors must comply with park pers
	onnel regarding stroller and wagon parking. \nFOOD AND BEVERAGES: Guests a
	re permitted to enter with one factory-sealed bottle of water. While outsi
	de food and drinks are prohibited\, exceptions will be made for baby food 
	and necessary medical dietary food items. A variety of food\, non-alcoholi
	c drinks\, beer\, and wine is available for purchase from Festival concess
	ionaires. \nRE-ENTRY: If you leave the Festival site\, you will be re-scre
	ened before re-entry. \nTHE FOLLOWING ARE PROHIBITED: \n\nSmoking or Vapin
	g\nUmbrellas\nDrug Use\nKites and Drones\nRecreational Motorized Vehicles\
	nGuns\, knives\, any weaponry\nSoliciting\nBikes\, scooters\, rollerblades
	\, and roller skates\n\nGroup Stage Festival Schedule: \nThursday\, June 1
	1 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – Mexico vs South Africa (2:00 p.m. Kick Of
	f) \nFriday\, June 12 from 6:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – USA vs Paraguay (8:00
	 p.m. Kick Off) \nThursday\, June 18 from 6:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – Mexico
	 vs South Korea (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nFriday\, June 19 from 12:30 p.m. to
	 5:30 p.m. – USA vs Australia (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nWednesday\, June 24 f
	rom 6:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – Czechia vs Mexico (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nRou
	nd of 32 Festival Schedule: \nSunday\, June 28 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m
	. – 2A vs 2B (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nWednesday\, July 1 from 5:30 p.m. to 1
	0:30 p.m. – 1D vs 3BEFIJ (7:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nRound of 16 Festival Sched
	ule: \nMonday\, July 6 from 5:30 p.m. to 10:30 p.m. – W81 vs W82 (7:00 p.m
	. Kick Off) \nQuarter-Finals Festival Schedule: \nThursday\, July 9 from 1
	:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. – W89 vs W90 (3:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nFriday\, July 10
	 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – W93 vs W94 (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nSaturday
	\, July 11 from 2:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – W91 vs W92 (4:00 p.m. Kick Off) 
	& W95 vs W96 (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nSemi-Finals Festival Schedule: \nTuesd
	ay\, July 14 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – W97 vs W98 (2:00 p.m. Kick Off
	) \nWednesday\, July 15 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – W99 vs W100 (2:00 p
	.m. Kick Off) \nFinals Festival Schedule: \nSaturday\, July 18 from 2:00 p
	.m. to 8:00 p.m. – Bronze Final (4:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nSunday\, July 19 fr
	om 12:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. – Final (2:00 p.m. Kick Off)\n\nhttps://www.lev
	yparkhouston.org/events/summer-soccer-celebration/\n\nFrom Levy Park Houst
	on
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/summer-soccer-celebration/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT936H
END:VEVENT
